<paragraph id="390236EBD051FFECC18AFBF6FC23629B" blockId="3.[136,1452,1056,1154]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">
Endemic to 
<collectingRegion id="FB79F809D051FFECC00BFBF6FEA86223" box="[265,372,1056,1082]" country="Australia" name="Tasmania" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">Tasmania</collectingRegion>
where it is a rare epiphyte in heathland at high elevations.It differs from the Northern Hemisphere’s 
<taxonomicName id="FEBD4D68D051FFECC18AFB92FDD06247" authority="(J. Lowe) Resl &amp; T. Sprib." authorityName="Resl &amp; T. Sprib." baseAuthorityName="J. Lowe" box="[136,524,1092,1118]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Xylographaceae" genus="Lambiella" kingdom="Fungi" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="caeca">
<emphasis id="0BC9EAF9D051FFECC18AFB92FF3B6244" box="[136,231,1092,1117]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">L. caeca</emphasis>
(J.Lowe) Resl &amp; T.Sprib.
</taxonomicName>
mainly in the dimensions of its ascospores, and thus its placement in 
<taxonomicName id="FEBD4D68D051FFECC422FB92FA4E6247" box="[1312,1426,1092,1118]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Xylographaceae" genus="Lambiella" kingdom="Fungi" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0BC9EAF9D051FFECC422FB92FA4E6247" box="[1312,1426,1092,1118]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">Lambiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unequivocal. 
<collectionCode id="5FACAE2ED051FFECC01FFBBEFEEC629B" box="[285,304,1128,1154]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15406" name="Harvard University - Arnold Arboretum" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" type="Herbarium">A</collectionCode>
full description and discussion is provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="5D2C4B1AD051FFECC239FBBEFC27629B" author="Kantvilas, G." box="[827,1019,1128,1154]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" pagination="349 - 364" refId="ref7624" refString="Kantvilas, G. (2014) New species of the genus Rimularia Nyl. from Tasmania. Lichenologist 46: 349 - 364. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0024282913000595" type="journal article" year="2014">Kantvilas (2014)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
